 <text id="B0803T">
  <front id="d2">
   <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
    <p>Haskill is urged to settle his account with Boston Lane.</p>
   </div1>
  </front>

  <body id="d4">

   <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
    <head>
     <abbr expan="Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">B R F &amp; A L.</abbr>
     <abbr expan="Office of 4th Division, 9th Sub-District">Off 4 Div 9 S. Dist</abbr>
     <name type="recipient">William Haskill</name>
    </head>

    <opener>
     <dateline>
      <date value="1867-05-30">May 30/67</date>
      <name type="place">"Bagby" <unclear>Fairie</unclear> near Staunton</name>
     </dateline>

     <salute/>
    </opener>

    <p>I have seen Boston Lane and his account with you shows that you are in his debt. You will
     call at this <pb n="2"/>office within 10 days and must allow him to secure balance of Corn due
     from Mr. Andrews.</p>

    <closer>
     <salute/>
     <signed><hi rend="underline">Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> P Jackson</hi><lb/>Agent</signed>
    </closer>
   </div1>
  </body>
 </text>
